.TH GOT-AUDIT 1 "2026-05-27" "got-audit 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
got-audit \- audit the Global Offset Table of running processes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B got-audit
.RB [ \-a | \-\-all ]
.RB [ \-h | \-\-help ]
.I PID
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B got-audit
attaches to a running process and examines its Global Offset Table (GOT) to detect
potential security issues such as symbol hijacking, namespace tampering, and unexpected
symbol resolution.

The tool parses ELF files using libelf, reads process memory via ptrace, and compares
GOT entries against symbol exports from loaded libraries. It reports warnings when:
.IP \(bu 2
A symbol is exported by multiple libraries (excluding known duplicates)
.IP \(bu 2
A symbol resolves to a library that does not export it
.PP
This helps identify LD_PRELOAD attacks, library injection, and other runtime exploitation
techniques that modify symbol resolution.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-a ", " \-\-all
Audit GOT for all mapped ELF objects in the process, not just the main executable.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help message and exit.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I PID
Process ID to audit. Must be a valid running process that the user has permission to
attach to via ptrace.
.SH OUTPUT
The tool displays a report for each audited ELF object showing:
.IP \(bu 2
GOT protection status (Full RelRO, Partial RelRO, or No RelRO)
.IP \(bu 2
Number of GOT function entries
.IP \(bu 2
Each symbol with its resolved library (color-coded: green for resolved, yellow for
unresolved)
.IP \(bu 2
Warnings in red for security issues
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
Error (invalid arguments, failed to attach, etc.)
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Audit the main executable of process 1234:
.RS
.B got-audit 1234
.RE
.PP
Audit all loaded libraries in process 1234:
.RS
.B got-audit \-\-all 1234
.RE
.SH SECURITY
This tool requires CAP_SYS_PTRACE capability or root privileges to attach to processes.
The target process is temporarily paused while attached.

Only audit processes you own or have explicit permission to inspect.
.SH KNOWN LIMITATIONS
.IP \(bu 2
Only supports ELF binaries
.IP \(bu 2
Tested on x86_64, i386, and aarch64 architectures
.IP \(bu 2
Target process must be running (cannot audit core dumps)
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /proc/PID/maps
Used to read process memory mappings
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR gdb (1),
.BR ldd (1),
.BR nm (1),
.BR objdump (1),
.BR readelf (1),
.BR ptrace (2),
.BR elf (5)
.SH ORIGIN
This tool is a C++ port of the
.B got-audit
command from GEF (GDB Enhanced Features), originally written in Python as a GDB plugin.
.SH AUTHOR
Ported from the GEF project.
